      • addPart

        public void addPart()
        This method runs when the Save button is pressed. This method handles input data validation, such as making sure the text fields are all filled out and have the proper data types associated with them. It also checks that min is less than max and inventory is greater than or equal to min and inventory is less than or equal to max. Once those conditions have been met, the program also has to check for the Radio Button groups, and make sure either InHouse or Outsourced has been pressed, and depending on that, a Part is generated using the InHouse class or the Outsourced Class. If everything has been met, and there are no errors, an alert is sent to the user, informing them that their change has been committed.
